<p>As part of its ongoing commitment to giving back, Teamwork Cares recently collected donations to support <a href="https://oldsmarcares.org/">Oldsmar Cares</a>, a volunteer-run nonprofit that has served Oldsmar and surrounding communities since 1997.</p>

<h2>A month of collecting essentials</h2>
<p>In the month of June, our team gathered donations of food and essential hygiene products, including macaroni and cheese, pasta, peanut butter, jelly, oatmeal, canned fruit, canned vegetables, canned beans, soup, deodorant, bug spray, toothpaste, shampoo, and soap. Items were collected and delivered by Melinda Muniz and Sarah Downes in the Clearwater office.</p>

<h2>Timed to meet a real need</h2>
<p>The drive was timed to meet a real need. Summer can be especially difficult for families facing food insecurity, as many children lose access to school meals while school is out.</p>

<h2>About Oldsmar Cares</h2>
<p>Since 1997, Oldsmar Cares has provided food, clothing, and other essential support to local families, all through the work of dedicated volunteers.</p>
<p>We're proud to support organizations that create real change in our community, and we look forward to continuing our partnership with Oldsmar Cares.</p>
